        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 4:24PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 424 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles west of Westview Circle, or 17 miles west of Wheatland, moving
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Westview Circle.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
southeastern Wyoming.</instruction>
